purpose: The Collective for the Advancement of Minority Medical Scientists (CAMMS) aims to:

name: College Democrats
purpose: College Democrats is the official voice of students within the Democratic Party. We serve as a meeting place for students to get involved in organizing and electoral politics as well as discuss progressive causes on UF's campus and the greater Gainesville community.

name: College of Liberal Arts and Sciences Ambassadors
purpose: The primary purpose of the Ambassadors of Liberal Arts and Sciences is to provide peer advising and ambassadorship to the College of Liberal Arts and Sciences by providing academic and career guidance under the direction of professional advisors and faculty of the College. This shall be fulfilled through bi-weekly meetings, various training initiatives, and collaboration with advisors from the Academic Advising Center. This organization is not for profit and non-commercial in nature.
category: Liberal Arts and Sciences, Ambassador, Professional/Career

name: College of Liberal Arts and Sciences Student Council
purpose: To act as a liaison for the faculty and students in the College of Liberal Arts & Sciences by providing student representatives for faculty committees, hosting a variety of workshops based on students' expressed needs, and facilitating a Mentor/Mentee program for undergraduates of the college.

name: College of Medicine Graduate Student Organization
purpose: 1. The COM-GSO provides a forum for graduate students at the College of Medicine to address issues involving faculty, curriculum, facilities, and policies at the Colleges of Medicine, Dentistry, Veterinary Medicine, and other associated colleges within the Health Sciences Center (HSC) and UF College of Medicine satellite sites. 2. The COM-GSO serves as an advisory board, sending representatives to the Medical College Council (MCC), BMS Concentration Coordinators, the College of Medicine Student Advocacy Committee (SAC), and the Graduate Student Council (GSC). 3. The COM-GSO works to facilitate graduate student organizations and activities that involve education, recruitment, and philanthropic efforts.

name: College of Medicine Student Government Association
purpose: The primary purpose of this organization is to provide a medium through which the needs and concerns of members of the College of Medicine can be discussed, addressed, and resolved. This organization will act as a liaison between its members and the College of Medicine, the University of Florida, and the Gainesville community. These goals shall be achieved through Executive Board and class meetings as well as organizing activities including academic, social, and community service...

name: College of Pharmacy Graduate Student Council
purpose: The purpose of the College of Pharmacy Graduate Student Council (COP GSC) is to facilitate an environment for College of Pharmacy graduate students to network and grow through engagement in both social and academic events, as well as serve as a liaison between faculty, administration, and graduate students in the College of Pharmacy.

name: College of Pharmacy Student Council - Gainesville
purpose: The College of Pharmacy Student Council at the Gainesville Campus focuses on maintaining communication between COP students, faculty, and student organizations through monthly GBMs and social events at the college.

name: College Of Pharmacy Student Council - Jacksonville
purpose: The purpose of Student Council College of Pharmacy – Jacksonville is: I. To represent the views and opinions of the students of the UFCOP to the Dean, faculty, administrative offices, and the University of Florida community. II. To report to our respective groups findings of our discussions and to report news of importance to the students and college faculty. III. To assist in the advancement of pharmaceutical education and professionalism through cooperation with the college faculty and administration. IV. To encourage and implement projects of interest and value to the students of the UFCOP. These events will be sponsored in accordance with Student Government regulations. V. Activities such as Service, Orientation, Student Directory, Peer Advisor, Award, Adopt-A-Road, and any other activities the Student Council College of Pharmacy – Jacksonville deems appropriate or necessary.

name: College of Pharmacy Student Council - Orlando Campus
purpose: A.To represent the views and opinions of the students of the COPORL to the Dean, faculty, administrative offices of the University of Florida College of Pharmacy, and to the University of Florida community.

name: College Republicans
purpose: We are the official voice of the Republican Party at the University‹ of Florida.

name: Collegiate Farm Bureau
purpose: To provide an opportunity for students interested in agricultural policy, education, leadership, and communication to explore problems of common interest. To develop an understanding of the opportunities and problems associated with the professions of agricultural policy, education, extension, leadership, and communications. To develop professional interests in the agricultural industry. To promote agricultural awareness for everyone and help out the community in any way we can. This includes but is not limited to involvement in Agriculture Awareness Days at elementary schools, numerous community service events, and connecting with industry professionals. To provide an opportunity for the development of leadership qualities that enable members to effectively participate in community organizations. To maintain close contact between Florida Farm Bureau and American Farm Bureau, as well as agricultural communicators, and other agribusiness and educational professionals at the University of Florida, in the College of Agricultural and Life Sciences (CALS), and throughout the state and nation.

name: Collegiate Veterans Society
purpose: The Collegiate Veterans Society (CVS) is dedicated to helping fellow veterans effectively transition from military to college life and to enriching the community and the campus with veteran-sponsored events.

name: Community Engagement Board
purpose: The Community Engagement Board is established for the purpose of putting on programs to bring students together and form lasting bonds and relationships throughout their time at the University of Florida.

name: Community Health Service Corps
purpose: We are a pre-health service organization focused on the elimination of health disparities in our community.

To provide educational opportunities for veterinary students relate to companion animal medicine through guest speakers, wet labs, and other formats. 3. To encourage camaraderie among veterinary students with an interest in companion animal medicine, behavior, or dentistry. 4. To allow mention of CABD membership on curriculum vitae to demonstrate interest in veterinary companion animal medicine.

In addition UFCC purpose gives the opportunity for individuals to establish positive relationships, practice teamwork and motivation as an extension to their athletic interest.

name: Creative Practice
purpose: Creative Practice is a group composed of medical students and faculty who believe that artistic expression is a vital part of medical education. Our purpose is to promote artistic expression in any number of ways among students and faculty as a means of enriching our lives and those of the patients that we help care for. We believe that art and creative expression should be included among the many credentials of a doctor. Creative Practice tries to highlight and encourage the continued creative expression of medical students. This expression can come in a wide variety of ways such as dancing, playing musical instruments or just making funny youtube videos. The goal of this club is to provide opportunities for students to practice art that may have otherwise be neglected in their busy lives.

name: Credit Club

Included in this pedagogy is the understanding of credit score, inquiries, debt, credit-cards, and travel rewards, in promotion of effective finance management.

name: Criminology and Law Honor Society

name: Critical Theory Reading Group
purpose: The critical theory reading group is an organization for graduate students to supplement their research with additional theory studies. We have monthly meetings in which we read 1-2 theory articles and discuss their arguments, implications, and applications to current events and our own individualized research.

name: Crohn's and Colitis Student Initiative
purpose: The Crohn's and Colitis Student Initiative (CCSI) is a support group made to serve college students with Inflammatory Bowel Disease. Inflammatory Bowel Disease consists of Crohn's Disease and Ulcerative Colitis and can be extremely hard to navigate throughout college. That is why this support group would serve as a place of solace for these students and allow them to express concerns with those suffering the same challenges as them. IBD is an invisible disease, meaning it is not apparent from the outside. These students with these diseases not only have to deal with the transition to a new school, but also how to manage their complicated disease at this school. Creating a group of individuals who understand exactly what they are going through can truly allow them to integrate themselves effectively at the University of Florida. They could either sit and listen to other students and how they manage their disease at school or share experiences that they need advice on/could potentially help others. College students with IBD are an at risk population so we hope to provide help in order to better manage their disease at school and improve their college experience.

name: CRU

We raise our funds through various fundraisers and donations and provide members with many volunteering events to engage with others in the community around us. We are a smaller organization that strives to make all members feel included and provide opportunities for everyone from all backgrounds.

name: CyberGator
purpose: CyberGatorz, a student organization affiliated with the University of Florida and the Florida Institute for Cybersecurity (FICS) Research, seeks to advance the field of cybersecurity through bringing together passionate future cybersecurity experts. Each student offers a unique perspective, building a diverse and well-rounded academic environment. CyberGatorz encompasses all areas of information and hardware security, from security of nanoelectronic devices, to integrated circuits and systems security, theoretical algorithms to internet-of-things, and larger cyber physical systems. CyberGatorz also hosts their Orange & Blue cHat series which aims to bring thoughtful discussion and inspire new students by bringing a resident expert to lead a relevant topic. We hope to offer other educational benefits such as tutorials, and certificates within the nation's premier multidisciplinary cybersecurity research institute. Most importantly, every CyberGator believes in fostering positive relationships with peers, mentors, industry experts, and future generations of STEM experts.

name: Dairy Science Club
purpose: The Dairy Science Club (DSC) promotes involvement in the dairy industry at the local, regional, and national levels, allowing students to make connections to peers and industry representatives. Members have opportunities to attend and present at conferences, participate in intercollegiate competitions, attend farm tours with experts in the field, and promote a positive public perception of the dairy industry through community outreach and volunteerism.

name: Dancin' Gator
purpose: Dancin' Gator is a unique dance team. We do not have auditions, and as a result, we have dancers of all levels, ranging from beginners to advanced performers. The purpose of our organization is to bring dancers of all levels together in an effort to maintain their passion for the performing arts. We hold weekly dance practices in preparation for an end of the semester performance. Dancers are also involved in choreographing routines and teaching dance steps to their fellow peers. Socials and fundraising events are also held each semester. Some of the different types of dances that we showcase include: hip hop, contemporary, tap, lyrical, salsa, step, kickline, jazz, Irish, Indian, etc.

name: Danza Dance Company

The company also performs at other events on and off campus. Danza was created with the intent to allow college students to continue their passion for dance while finding their niche in such a large and incredible university and has done just that for over 20 years.

As we work together to blur the line between daydream and every day, fact and fiction, we intend to move toward the reality of a world that recognizes, celebrates, and cherishes our differences. We aim to create the DayDream Magazine as a collaborative effort with the community and the environment, reaching out to the people who make up the surrounding community and producing this magazine on a digital electronic magazine platform.

name: Dominican Student Association

Additionally, we host monthly General Body Meetings, social events, and have a full week of activities in the Spring to celebrate our Independence day. Join us!

We will be conducting these workshops and be affiliated with Gigi's Playhouse in Gainesville, FL.

Our team works alongside physicians, nurses, child-life specialists, and PT/OT to create engineering devices to impact the patient experience. Dream Team Engineering is currently composed of five individual teams that are tasked with developing specific technologies that will be used in-hospital to improve the experience for patients at Shands.

name: Ecuadorian Culture and Heritage Association
purpose: The purpose of the Ecuadorian Culture and Heritage Association at the University of Florida is to bring undergraduate students at the University of Florida that are interested in learning about Ecuadorian culture, heritage, and history together and educate them on these topics through monthly informational meetings and cultural awareness events throughout the academic year. The organization will serve as a point of contact for all undergraduate Ecuadorian and non-Ecuadorian students who wish to engage in leadership opportunities and cultural partnerships with the Hispanic Student Association, its affiliates, and other organizations within the University of Florida. The organization will also serve as a way to bring to light important topics that need further discussion in the Ecuadorian context such as the status of Afro-Ecuadorians, Indigenous Ecuadorians, and LGBTQ+ Ecuadorians within Ecuador and how their lives are constantly affected within the culture of Ecuadorian society. The organization also aims to inform students of current political situations occurring in Ecuador as the nation undergoes changes and affects the lives of Ecuadorians both on the mainland, and abroad. This organization shall not be for-profit and shall be non-commercial in nature.

Our core values will be generosity, education, and commitment; we will work towards providing aid to the world's most impactful charities, commit to a stated level of generosity for the rest of our lives, and continuously educate ourselves on best practices within effective altruism and the greater philanthropy landscape.

Through continuous interaction, the EGSC seeks to increase the quality of education delivered, workforce competence of graduating students, and the overall reputation of the University of Florida.

name: Equity, Diversity, and Inclusion in Sustainability

We will do this by providing an inclusive environment for diverse and thoughtful discussion to help expand the knowledge of budding sustainability change-makers. We will also act as a platform to amplify the voices of marginalized and underrepresented communities. Our mission is to educate others on sustainability and service affected communities in the fight to ensure that the benefits of any future changes are shared equitably. To fulfill this mission, we will be working with upcoming community rejuvenation projects in the city of Gainesville as well as meeting with sustainability professors to help diversify their courses.

It is founded on the principles that the state exists to preserve freedom, that the separation of governmental powers is central to our Constitution, and that it is emphatically the province and duty of the judiciary to say what the law is, not what it should be. The Society seeks both to promote an awareness of these principles and to further their application through its activities.

In an effort to develop the versatile leaders of tomorrow, we cultivate an environment rich in resilience and diplomacy. This will be accomplished through bi-weekly general body meetings, outreach and social events, and professional guest speakers.

name: First Generation Organization

name: First-Generation Lawyers
purpose: The organization's goal is to provide first-generation Pre-Law undergraduate students at the University of Florida with the tools necessary to successfully navigate the law school admissions process and their future career in the legal field. Through meetings, panels, workshops, and guest speakers, valuable information will be provided to UF's Pre-Law students. This organization is based on equality, inclusion, respect, and professionalism. First-Generation Lawyers will function as a safe space in which all first-generation pre-law students can find an inclusive community within campus. Overall, this organization's purpose is to provide future aspiring legal professionals the tools they may need to successfully overcome any obstacles or challenges that may present to first-generation pre-law undergraduate students.

purpose: The First-Year Leadership Program exists to: A. Foster an enduring awareness and unity among Asian and Asian Americans at the University of Florida B. This organization acts as a voice for the graduate students at both the Program and University levels and provides and promotes professional development. purpose: Florida Actuarial Student Society (FASS) is a student-run organization dedicated to informing students about the actuarial profession and helping them network with their peers. purpose: The Florida Museum Student Association (FMSA) was created to serve, connect, and engage students in the Florida Museum and greater UF campus. Founded by a museum PhD student, Adania Flemming, in spring 2019, our association formed to give students who have a passion for natural history collections a place to both connect with one another and develop skills, knowledge, and participate in opportunities afforded by proximity and access to an on-campus natural history museum. The purpose of FMSA is to ensure students within the FLMNH are able to capitalize on all opportunities provided by the FLMNH, both in their program of studies and throughout their post-graduation careers. We hope to be able to work with the faculty to establish a transparent governance system in the Department of Natural History, giving agency to FLMNH students.

purpose: Florida Running Club has been created as a competitive group of athletes that aim to be a top cross country and track club in the nation. To reach this goal, the club will compete nationally against other top clubs when possible, including at NIRCA Regionals and Nationals for Cross Country and at NCAA sponsored meets or races with NCAA teams for Track and Field. The club will also compete against varsity squads from D-I, D-II, D-III, and NAIA as preparation for those major races. Funds for the club will be raised through key sponsorships and various other fundraising activities, as well as through funding from the University of Florida. The club also will maintain its status as a Registered Student Organization (RSO). https://orgs.studentinvolvement.ufl.edu/Forms/sport-clubs

name: Florida Society of Health-System Pharmacists-Student Division Jacksonville
purpose: 1. The purpose of the Florida Society of Health-System Pharmacists is to represent its members and to provide leadership to enable its members practicing in organized healthcare settings to: (1) provide high quality pharmaceutical care services that foster the efficacy, safety and cost effectiveness of medication use; (2) contribute to programs and services that emphasize the health needs of the public and the prevention of disease; (3) promote pharmacy as an essential component of the healthcare team. 2. The purpose of the student society is to make students aware of pharmacy practice in health systems; provide information to students about career directions in and credentials needed for pharmacy practice in health systems; and encourage membership and participation in the Florida Society of Health-System Pharmacists (FSHP) and the American Society of Health-System Pharmacists (ASHP) as a student and upon graduation.

name: Florida Society of the Social Sciences
purpose: F3S is led by graduate students at UF who aim to (1) cross-fertilize the social and humanistic sciences in Florida, and (2) provide spaces where emerging scholars can grow and cooperate while promoting social justice, (3) provide opportunities for all students to develop their professional skills and research agendas.

name: Florida Student Branch of the American Society of Agricultural and Biological Engineers
purpose: The objective of ASABE is to encourage professional, technical, and social development of University of Florida (UF) students through such membership opportunities as: creating a closer relationship among students, faculty, and staff; committee membership; leadership development; national and international competitions; and community service.

name: Florida Students for Lifestyle Medicine
purpose: The purpose of FSLM is to promote UF undergraduate students to study health and wellness in a holistic model.Functional medicine looks at the root cause of disease and wellness, taking amultidisciplinary evidence based approach of the human body through genetic, lifestyle,and environmental practice through the use of a patient-centered approach. Furtheralthough integrative and functional medicine have many similarities in that they bothlook at the body in a holistic way, functional medicine is distinct in it's patient-centeredapproach that strives to explores a patient's individual biochemistry and why the patientis ill through a systems-oriented medical approach. The field of functional medicinefurther strives to understand the underlying root causes of each chronic disease throughdetailed investigations of an individual's genetic make-up. This opposes the traditionalacute care approach of treating symptoms and diseases instead of addressing the rootcause of illness. Gators for functional medicine is fostering the idea to take an systems oriented, patient-centered approach to the medical model to better address the needs forthe 21st century. Through our club, students will be able to apply knowledge throughoutthere future educations and careers as health care practitioners by having additionalskills and competencies of assessing complex causes of illnesses of which traditionalacademia does not provide. The function of the club will be to provide students withopportunities to spark conversation and comprehension of the different concepts ofevidence based functional medicine.
category: Healthy Living, Medicine, Health and Human Performance

name: Florida Swing Dancing Club
purpose: The goal of our club is to teach and spread the joy of swing dancing (Lindy Hop) across the Gainesville and University of Florida community. We travel and connect with others across the United States at Lindy Hop exchanges and workshops.

name: Florida TrailGator
purpose: The purpose of Florida TrailGator is to promote physical activity and well being through trail running and hiking on nature trails around Gainesville. Its purpose is extended to fostering an appreciation and awareness of the nature located in or near Gainesville. Members will build camaraderie with fellow exercise enthusiasts; trail running, hiking, and local nature outings will serve as our platform. When applicable, Florida TrailGator will contribute to the maintenance of natural settings in Gainesville.

name: Florida Women in Business
purpose: Florida Women in Business is a professional development organization that gives women the tools to succeed and break down barriers in college and beyond. Our vision is to empower women in a supportive environment and provide each member a unique experience. For example, our Mentor/Mentee program offers you a one-on-one relationship with a veteran FWIB member whose goal is to help you find your passion and be an advocate for your success. We also offer various committees that help you develop your strengths. Finally, we have inspiring speakers from prominent companies and the community who will offer their personal experiences and advice. When you join Florida Women in Business, you know you're joining a family of dynamic women who will help you in all of your endeavors and will cheer you on every step of the way.

name: Floridance
purpose: Floridance is the University's original student run dance company. We specialize in almost every style of dance including ballet, hip-hop, jazz, contemporary, modern, and tap! We pride ourselves in creating a family-like atmosphere for all of our dancers by incorporating socials and community volunteering. We are a performance based company, and any member has the opportunity to choreograph a solo, small group, or large group piece for our bi-annual showcase.

name: Food Animal Club (SCAABP)
purpose: The purpose of this club is to broaden experiences of veterinary students interested in food animal medicine while providing opportunities beyond the vet school curriculum.

name: Food Recovery Network
purpose: The Food Recovery Network was established to implement hunger relief programs for communities and improving the sustainability of local restaurants, schools and other organizations that conduct food service. The Food Recovery Network also aims to provide sustainability and nutrition education to the community. Our goal is making a lasting impact on the reduction of food waste and food insecurity.

name: Food Science and Human Nutrition Club
purpose: To promote and share knowledge of food science, dietetics, and nutritional sciences throughout the UF and Gainesville community. To serve as a resource to students to develop professional knowledge of food science, dietetics, and nutritional sciences. To serve the local community through education of healthy eating practices and food production.

name: Footprints Buddy and Support Program
purpose: Footprints is a student-run volunteering and community service organization benefiting UF Health Shands Children's Hospital and the local Gainesville community. We have members volunteering everyday of the week from 9 a.m. - 7 p.m. in the Pediatric Immunocompromised and Infusion units. By engaging kids in one-on-one play, we strive to help “kids just be kids” during treatments. This can come in the form of crazy arts & crafts projects, legendary Mario Kart tournaments (just ask some of our members about how intense it can get), playing pretend, and much more. You never know what you're going to end up doing on a hospital day. Besides playing with the kiddos on the unit, Footprints volunteers in the community with various community partners and foundations who are all aligned with the same cause of supporting the kids and families affected by pediatric illness. Lastly, one of our primary goals is to create a close-knit atmosphere among members through social events, a mentorship program, and general body meetings. We don't consider ourselves as just an organization, but a family too.

name: Forensic Science Association
purpose: This organization encourages unity among all students who are interested in forensic science. The Forensic Science Association offers students the opportunity to enrich their educational curriculum through contact with agencies and individuals who have professional experience in the field. FSA will provide resources for obtaining careers and inform students about various professions and opportunities across a broad range of disciplines within forensic science. FSA will facilitate opportunities for students to network with professionals, academic authorities, other students, graduates, and the community. FSA strives to foster a general feeling of community among its members and aids students in developing professional competencies.

name: Forestry Graduate Student Organization
purpose: The purpose of FGSO is to provide a sense of community within the School of Forest Resources and Conservation, and provide professional and networking opportunities to graduate students.

name: Formula Electric
purpose: The Purpose of this organization is to promote interest in research, development, design, construction, and operation of electric vehicles, to further familiarize students with career opportunities in this area, and to further the educational and personal development of students. As Formula Electric grows it shall strive for more challenging designs and branch deeper into engineering disciplines such as control systems and machine learning. The organization may accomplish its goals by inviting speakers from industry, organizing tours of facilities engaged in this area of work, entering the Formula SAE Electric competition, and organizing social events for its members.

name: French Club: le cercle francais
purpose: French Club thrives to offer an educational experience for anyone interested in French culture. Besides conversation sessions and tutoring for French speakers, Le Cercle FranĂ§ais will host many events and activities for everyone to enjoy.

name: Freshman Leadership Council
purpose: The primary goal of the Freshmen Leadership Council is to provide personal, professional, and leadership growth opportunities for a select group of freshmen. These goals will be accomplished through A year long curriculum in which every Wednesday the 50 council members and director team (consisting of: Chairperson, Vice Chair of Membership, Director of Membership, Vice Chair of Programming, 5 Programming Directors, Vice Chair of Communications, Director of External Communication, Director of Internal Communication, Vice Chair of Operations, Director of Finances, and Director of Internal Relations) come together for a weekly alloted time to follow the curriculum that will be established by the Vice Chair of Membership and the Director of Membership. This curriculum is split into two semesters (Fall and Spring), the meetings use speakers and interactive activities to promote the desired lesson for the meeting. The lessons focus on leadership, professional development, and personal growth.

name: Freshman Leadership Engineering Group
purpose: Our mission is to build well-rounded Gator engineers who exemplify the values of leadership, passion, and growth through service to their college and community.

name: Friends for Life of America
purpose: Friends for Life of America is a student-run organization devoted to making a difference in the lives of children with cancer and their families through raising money for a charity and awareness of pediatric cancer.

name: Friends of MSF Gainesville Chapter
purpose: Our organization aims to promote awareness of global health issues and the international organization, Doctors Without Borders/MĂ©decins Sans FrontiĂ¨res', humanitarian work. This club will participate in various fundraising activities, as well as provide opportunities for our members to be better prepared for their future careers in healthcare via service events, skills clinics, guest speakers, etc. We welcome all pre-health students, or anyone interested!

name: Future Black Men in Medicine
purpose: To inform and educate African American males who attend the University of Florida on the multiple pathways that they could explore during their journey in medicine. They can learn about the different paths, and explore different opportunities that could answer questions that they may have. Allowing for a smoother transition into medical school.

name: Future Business Leaders of America - Phi Beta Lambda
purpose: FBLA-PBL is an organization that is there for YOU. Here at the UF chapter, we strive to promote career related opportunities and build a community of leaders - all while giving back to UF and the local community. In addition to workshops, socials, and community service activities UF's PBL also competes in a variety of competitions on the state and national level. Any student is eligible to compete and prizes range from medals and trophies to up to $1,200 per competition on the national level. For more information and a list of available competitions, please visit our website or Facebook page!

name: Future Florida Neurosurgeons
purpose: Future Florida Neurosurgeons' primary purpose is to expose forward-thinking students to the highly competitive fields of neurosurgery and neurology. We will offer meetings with highly ranked professionals in the neurological field and hold discussions of new processes, techniques, and mechanisms of illness. Overall, we hope to provide an opportunity for students to understand, in great detail, the numerous opportunities that are provided by the field of neurology and neurosurgery and how they operate on a daily basis.

name: Gainesville For All Chapter
purpose: "The purpose of this organization is to connect the University of Florida students with their off-campus community through involvement in learning about and actively seeking meaningful solutions to systemic persistent problems of race and poverty in Gainesville especially concerning areas of health and transportation, family support, education, and criminal justice. This will be done through community meetings, volunteer events, and discussion forums, etc. The goal of this chapter is to change negative patterns occurring in marginalized populations due to poverty and other discriminations through direct grassroots activism alongside GNV4ALL Inc., a local nonprofit 501(c)(3) organization

name: Gainesville Hillel
purpose: Hillel is an organization that inspires future leaders to positively impact the world through a Jewish lens by connecting them with Israel, travel experiences, spirituality, doing good, career advancement opportunities, and entrepreneurial endeavors. We strive to create a sense of community for all students. Our mantra is "Tradition, Inspiration, Activation" and we'd love to help you learn why.

name: Gainesville Political Action Committee
purpose: The Gainesville Political Action Committee is a student-led initiative that actively advocates for a better Gainesville community through hosting and planning our own projects, petitions, town halls, seminars, panels, protests, and other advocacy events. Founded on the principles of solidarity and justice, we fight for what's right by educating others on topics considering environmentalism, equity, and human rights and using that education as a basis for further political action. Our members take lead on projects that they personally care about, and we make our initiatives accessible and actionable to a wide student basis. By creating and hosting our own events, we try to keep the people of Gainesville informed about current social issues and give them the resources to fight the injustices they see around them. GPAC separates itself from the other organizations on UF's campus by being very active and involved in the kinds of advocacy it partakes in. Instead of compiling resources for members to get personally interested in, GPAC prefers to create their own resources, whether that means creating graphics that illustrate the recycling rules of Gainesville or reaching out to local nonprofits to present on the work that they do and how that work can be extended to other Gainesville organizations. GPAC aims to become a staple of the Gainesville community, a place where people go to not just for reliable sociopolitical information, but also a place where they can feel empowered and inspired to create the change they want to see in the world.

name: Game Developers' Association
purpose: The Game Developers' Association exists to assemble a community of UF students interested in game development! We preserve a positive environment where beginners can learn game development, anyone can show off their personal work, and where partnerships in both personal projects and game jams can emerge!

name: GAMMA ETA
purpose: Gamma Eta Sorority, Inc. is a diverse sorority that aims to foster strong female leadership within the University of Florida campus. We challenge our members to help them reach their maximum potential. We are a social sorority that stands for the pillars of sisterhood, service, strength, scholarship, leadership, unity, and diversity. We seek to make a mark on this campus and on each other.

name: GAMMA PHI BETA
purpose: The purpose of the Gamma Phi Beta is to support and inspire the lifelong development of women.

name: Gastro Student Association
purpose: The purpose of our club contains three pillars consisting of support, service, and guidance. Being diagnosed with IBS/IBD and other gastrointestinal ailments impede students and people everyday that forces us to deviate from a “normal” life. In the first pillar, support, students now will have a place for them to realize that they are not facing these issues alone, and to help further facilitate students to reach their goals in their academic endeavors. The second pillar, service, will be dedicated to help the community become more aware about these disorders. In addition, raise money through events consisting of, but not limited to, marathons, cycling/biking, sales, etc. to raise money for foundations such as the Crohn's and Colitis Foundation to aid further scientific advancements to find a cure. This is in addition to catering to the community by volunteering at medical facilities or even supporting patients going through similar disorders in times of distress. Furthermore, advocacy for these disorders by pushing legislature at the University of Florida to make the university as inclusive as possible if seen fit. The third pillar, guidance, encompasses the idea that when students face these disorders they are oftentimes faced with obstacles associated with nutrition, social life, academically, etc. This organization will provide a learning experience for everyone to implement healthy lifestyles to help make these disorders more manageable.

name: Gator Against Poverty
purpose: The purpose of the Gator Against Poverty is to draw attention to and alleviate the issue of poverty in the University of Florida student and faculty community, through the pillars of homelessness, hunger, and health.
category: Community/Volunteer Service, Social and Global Change

name: Gator Alliance for World Health
purpose: Gator Alliance for World Health aims to not only shed light on health disparities at large in our communities but also around the world. We strive to provide our members with the tools to not only become more educated and aware but also with the opportunities to make a difference both at home in our local community through volunteering events as well as globally with our drives and annual medical aid trip.

name: Gator Amateur Radio Club
purpose: Promote international goodwill through communicating with other amateur radio operators, further the art of radio through experimentation and research, and provide infrastructure in case of an emergency.

name: Gator Anime
purpose: We at Gator Anime provide a social space to enjoy Japanese anime and pop culture, host anime-related events and contests, as well as hold the annual SwampCon convention in the Reitz Union!

name: Gator Badminton Club
purpose: To provide a welcoming atmosphere, collective practice, and widespread competition of badminton enthusiasts and all interested participants throughout the University of Florida.

name: Gator BassMasters
purpose: Gator BassMasters serves as a competitive, collegiate bass fishing club, allowing University of Florida students the chance to compete against some of the best colleges in the nation in order to bring bass fishing titles to the university.

name: Gator Beach Volleyball
purpose: https://orgs.studentinvolvement.ufl.edu/Forms/sport-clubs

name: Gator Bhangra
purpose: The purpose of the organization is to promote the practice and performance of Bhangra, a traditional folk dance that originates from the Punjab region of India, on our campus here at the University of Florida.

name: Gator Billiards Club
purpose: Gator Billiards Club seeks to give members opportunities to play pool and meet new people. All skill levels are welcome.

name: Gator Brazilian Jiu Jitsu
purpose: Our purpose is to provide a welcoming, fun, and safe environment for anyone that wants to practice Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu. Both experienced and new members are always welcome to come learn and drill techniques, as well as apply them through free rolling!

name: Gator Chapter of the American Indian Science and Engineering Society
purpose: The purpose of the Gator Chapter of the American Indian Science and Engineering Society is to provide a sense of community for Indigenous students on campus and to raise awareness of Indigenous culture on campus. The goal of the student organization is to substantially increase the representation of American Indians, Alaska Natives, Native Hawaiians, Pacific Islanders, First Nations and other indigenous peoples of North America in science, technology, engineering and math (STEM) studies and careers.

name: Gator Chapter of the College Diabetes Network
purpose: The purpose of the Gator Chapter of the College Diabetes Network is to empower and improve the lives of students living with type one diabetes through peer support, social activities, and informational meetings.

name: Gator Chapter of the National Society of Black Physicists
purpose: The purpose of this chapter is to promote the professional development and well-being of Blacks pursuing degrees in physics within the local scientific community and region at large. This chapter seeks to develop and support efforts to increase opportunities, activities, and programs for Blacks in physics. The Chapter seeks to provide a non-partisan platform for major issues of scientific and cultural significance to its membership. Most importantly, the Chapter aims to establish a more connected, personal, and engaged community for the student members of the National Society of Black Physicists (NSBP).

name: Gator Chess Club
purpose: Allows a place for students who wish to play or learn chess to come weekly. Compete for the University of Florida by representing the school in national events. Club Discord: https://discord.gg/9yBSDKP Lichess Group: https://lichess.org/team/gator-chess-club

name: Gator Christian Life
purpose: Bringing college students to Jesus Christ and preparing them for a lifetime of service.

name: Gator Coalition of Occupational Therapy Advocates for Diversity Chapter
purpose: The Gator COTAD Chapter seeks to address issues surrounding diversity and inclusion within the field of occupational therapy. This means addressing the lack of diversity amongst therapy providers as well as encouraging those from under-served communities to seek occupational therapy and related healthcare services, and/or empowering them to enter the field of occupational therapy. We also seek to educate the current student body about occupational therapy and its benefits, as well as cultural humility and struggles faced by marginalized groups.

name: Gator Comics
purpose: The purpose of the organization is to provide a welcoming and fun environment for students to meet new people with one shared interest: comics. The organization is centered around comic books (both indie and mainstream), graphic novels, Japanese manga, and all related media including Marvel films and DC Comics television shows. We aim to hold social events and collaborate with other student organizations to promote the enjoyment of all comic material and provide a safe space for students to share their interests. With the large umbrella of graphic novels and comics being intimidating at times, Gator Comics aims to make it easier to get into the hobby by providing a completely free digital and physical library of comics. Lastly, Gator Comics will also promote exploration of the academic study of comics at the undergraduate and graduate levels.

name: Gator Cricket Club
purpose: https://orgs.studentinvolvement.ufl.edu/Forms/sport-clubs The purpose of Gator Cricket Club is to introduce and promote the game of cricket among UF students. GCC will teach new players how to play the game and understand the rules of the game. We aim to introduce cricket to the UF sports culture by holding practice and game sessions weekly. We like to invite everyone with an interest to play and participate.

name: Gator Criminology Syndicate
purpose: Purpose statement: To promote the interests of graduate students in the University of Florida's Criminology, Law and Society Program by facilitating communication between Criminology graduate students, faculty, and administration; raising funds in support of student activities and initiatives; providing assistance and mentoring to incoming Criminology graduate students; holding periodic meetings (3 per semester) to discuss official business and inform Criminology graduate students of events of interest; and promoting opportunities for professional development.

name: Gator Disc Golf
purpose: The purpose of Gator Disc Golf is to unite students of all levels with the love to disc golf in an accepting environment. We are dedicated to learning and improving our performance in the sport while striving to grow socially and professionally.

name: Gator Esports
purpose: The mission of Gator Esports is to foster an esports community at UF that provides students with a collaborative environment and collegiate level competition.

name: Gator for Haven Hospice
purpose: To provide support, care, and compassion to patients diagnosed with a terminal illness.

name: Gator for MUSIC (Music Instruction in the Community)
purpose: The purpose of Gator for MUSIC is to provide music lessons as a volunteering service to population groups that may not have the means to find a formal music teacher, and to provide a platform to engage in and promote casual music pedagogy and mentorship.

name: Gator for ReadingPals
purpose: The purpose of Gator for Reading Pals is to enhance the literacy skills of students in the Gainesville area, focusing primarily on students in disadvantaged populations. The goal for volunteers in Gator for Reading Pals is to mentor and build relationships with elementary-aged students in order to help them understand the importance of reading.

name: Gator for Refugee Medical Relief
purpose: Gator for Refugee Medical Relief is established for the purpose of raising medical resources, educational assistance, and awareness for in-need refugees and their families, locally and abroad.
category: Community/Volunteer Service, Social and Global Change

name: Gator for UNICEF
purpose: The United Nations Children's Fund is mandated by the United Nations to protect the rights of children, provide them with basic needs, and expand their opportunities to reach their full potential as members of society. The UNICEF Campus Initiative is a growing grassroots movement whose belief is that college students play a vital role in helping protect the world's children. Gator for UNICEF works to: 1. Educate people about issues affecting children. 2. Advocate policies that will help children worldwide. 3. Hold fundraisers to raise money for UNICEF USA. Since our instatement as a club in 2010, we have been involved in many projects and fundraisers such as Trick-or-Treat for UNICEF, World AIDS Day, World Water Week, Project Makeover and so much more. So come out and see what we're all about, and find one more reason why it's great to be a Florida Gator!
category: Community/Volunteer Service, Political Interests, Social and Global Change

name: Gator Gaming
purpose: The premier video gaming club.

name: Gator Genetics
purpose: To inform all fellow students about the application of genetics in a multitude of fields such as agriculture, medicine, biochemistry, etc. Additionally, we work to inform our fellow peers about promising career fields that require an extensive knowledge of genetics. Lastly our organization seeks to better the Gainesville community through multiple service opportunities.

name: Gator Gladiators
purpose: Our mission is to build a team of Gator Engineers who will work together to design, assemble, and program a robot which will be used to compete in the All Japan Robot-Sumo Tournament. Members will utilize skills obtained across various disciplines within the department of engineering to enhance their understanding of material as well as engage in the design process from start to finish. We aim to create an inclusive team that is well versed in the latest electrical, mechanical, and software trends in order to represent our university and our country with the highest standard.

name: Gator Guard Drill Team
purpose: The Gator Guard Drill Team is a ceremonial and competitive unit that represents and performs in accordance with the U.S. Army regulations. It's main mission is to provide and teach leadership and teamwork framework while also conducting regulation and exhibition drill and ceremonies.

name: Gator Humans versus Zombies
purpose: We are a diverse community that runs the stress relieving, internationally recognized game of Humans versus Zombies (HvZ). HvZ is a zombie simulation game of tag with nerf blasters, socks, and an immersive story.

name: Gator Judo
purpose: Our purpose is to provide a safe and competitive environment to practice and learn Judo. Participation Agreement: https://orgs.studentinvolvement.ufl.edu/Forms/sport-clubs.

name: Gator Juggling Club
purpose: To create a safe, fun and engaging environment to practice and teach the art of juggling on campus.

name: Gator Law American Civil Liberties Union
purpose: The American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) University of Florida Levin College of Law Chapter strives to provide a forum for students interested in issues pertaining to first amendment rights, equal protection rights, due process rights, privacy rights, and all other civil liberties. This chapter also advocates for legal protections for traditionally marginalized and vulnerable groups including women, people of color, members of the LGBTQ community, people with disabilities, and the poor. This chapter also serves as an informational resource, providing Law School students with details on civil liberty events around campus and in the greater Gainesville area. Our mission is to connect members with local, state and national ACLU chapters to assist these chapters' efforts and to gain pro bono and internship experience. The national network of the ACLU, through courts, legislatures and communities, defends and preserves the fundamental rights and liberties guaranteed by the Constitution and laws of the United States. This chapter seeks to aid in these noble efforts.
category: Law, Political Interests, Social and Global Change

name: Gator Major-4-Major Mentorship Program
purpose: The Gator Major-4-Major Mentorship programs value inclusiveness, togetherness, leadership, and friendship. The function of this program is for the mentor to provide an easier transition for the incoming university student by serving as a guiding figure. Each freshman and transfer student at the University of Florida who chooses to participate in this mentorship program will be paired with a Junior or Senior in the same College/ Department studying the same major. The ideal goal is for the mentor to guide and provide advice to the mentee about courses and the university environment in general. Through this relationship the program will make sure that incoming students at the University of Florida feel welcome and have familiarity with their courses and surrounding.

name: Gator McKnights Unite
purpose: To serve the UF graduate and undergraduate student community through professional and personal development opportunities and community outreach.

name: Gator Music Industry Club
purpose: The purpose of the Gator Music Industry Club (MIC) is to provide opportunities for future industry professionals and artists alike to learn from media, music, and entertainment industry professionals via panels and Q&As.

name: Gator Muslim Law Students Association
purpose: Connect Muslim students with one another and foster a sense of community and inclusion. The organization will connect its members with Muslim attorneys that will share their experiences in the legal system and how to navigate the legal field as Muslims practicing law. MLSA's goal is to influence the legal community to bring about meaningful change to meet the needs of the Muslim community. MLSA will organize events surrounding Islamic culture such as Ramadan iftar, Eid celebrations, and multicultural festivities.

name: Gator of Tomorrow
purpose: The Gator of Tomorrow Leadership Organization recognizes first year students at the University of Florida seeking to make major accomplishments both on campus and in the community. We are an honorarium that aims to empower our freshmen leaders to discover their unique leadership style and utilize their strengths to develop professionally, grow personally, and empower others in the process. Gator of Tomorrow members create invaluable relationships with students and alumni to expand their network and leadership abilities as well as to represent involvement in the UF community.

name: Gator Outreach Mentorship Program
purpose: The purpose of the Gator Outreach Mentorship Program is to connect mentors with high school students to give advice and guidance. This will be accomplished through forming one-on-one mentorships that meet once per week for one semester.

name: Gator Pals
purpose: Gator Pals (GP) is a student-run organization that volunteers at Sidney Lanier, a local school for students of varying abilities. GP members volunteer their time with students who have intellectual, developmental, emotional-behavioral, and other related disabilities. We attend the 50 minute P.E. periods and play all kinds of fun sports or physical activities with the students! Experience is not necessary. Our other volunteering program is through T.B. McPherson Recreation Center. We offer tutoring at the Florida gym on Mondays, Tuesday, and Wednesdays in the evenings. The children we tutor are from all over Alachua County Public school systems.

name: Gator Pharmacy Wellness - Gainesville
purpose: GPW aims to educate, support, and encourage the fundamentals of fitness, health, and nutrition in the UF College of Pharmacy and the community at large.

name: Gator Pharmacy Wellness - Jacksonville Campus
purpose: 1. To encourage all student pharmacists to become more knowledgeable about fitness, health and nutrition for patients and themselves.2. To encourage all student pharmacists to recognize the pharmacist's role in patient wellness concerning the fitness, health and nutrition for populations with specific disease states. 3. To encourage all student pharmacists to maintain good fitness, health and nutrition while advancing through pharmacy school .

name: Gator Pickleball
purpose: Gator Pickleball primary purpose is to provide students with an outlet to learn more about the sport of pickleball, regardless of experience, and to create connections between the different colleges of the University of Florida. Gator Pickleball will host a variety of events, meetings, and workshops for members to engage with each other and campus.

name: Gator Powerlifting
purpose: The purpose of Gator Powerlifting is to provide a safe and supportive community for powerlifters at the University of Florida, where athletes can train and compete together. Beyond lifting weights, we maintain the belief of uplifting others through community development.

name: Gator Pre-medical Guide
purpose: The GPG was born from the collaborative efforts of a group of University of Florida premed students who wanted a way not only to connect to their university through a shared interest, but to impart their knowledge on other students looking for a way to learn, read and write about medicine in all subjects. At one point, we were all freshman. We know what it's like to be thrown into a competitive pool of students at one of the nation's largest universities. We also know how intimidating that can be, and we're hoping our efforts into this project can give you the edge that we didn't have when we began our collegiate experience. Even for those with a few years under your belts, we would like this guide to serve as a helpful tool for choosing a medical school, studying for the MCAT, and keeping abreast of news in medicine. This publication is for you, premed students – written with your interests in mind by peers who wish to help you unlock all the keys to success to thrive here at UF as well as foster an ever-growing interest in medicine. We hope that you can utilize all the resources we offer to your advantage. Good luck to you all here at UF and in your future endeavors.Sincerely,The Gator Premedical Guide Staff

name: Gator Resonance
purpose: Gator Resonance has come into being in order to enrich the musical diversity of campus. The group comprises students who organize live music performance, consisting of covers of popular songs and a blend of classical Indian music with light music and other international genres. The purpose is to develop appreciation for commonalities in music from different parts of the world and bring them together by composing fusion with Indian classical and Indian light music.

name: Gator Robotics
purpose: The purpose of Gator Robotics is to encourage, inspire, and assist students of all disciplines and backgrounds by giving them the opportunity to design, build, and have fun with robots.

name: Gator Roller Derby
purpose: The purpose of Gator Roller Derby is to share the sport of flat track roller derby with the University of Florida community by providing the skills and training necessary to play, referee, officiate and/or compete in roller derby. We will accomplish this through weekly on- or off-skates practices focused on roller derby-related drills, off-skates fitness, and learning the rules of flat track roller derby; a new skater curriculum that provides progression pathways catered to individual team members; and intra-organizational scrimmaging appropriate for each participant's development level. This organization aims to empower women, men, and gender-expansive individuals through teamwork and leadership and their physical, mental and social health. We also strive to improve our local Gainesville community through service.

name: Gator Safety Professionals
purpose: Gator Safety Professionals is a non-political and a non-religious organization solely created to: organize student involvement with academic programs, provide mentoring for new or existing students, and to create, organize, or manage professional gatherings and social events with a focus on increasing safety education and awareness in construction-related majors.

name: Gator Salsa Club
purpose: Want a new hobby? Want to meet new people? Do you love salsa? Are you interested in taking dance classes for FREE?!?! Then this is the group for YOU!! No experience? No partner? No problem!!!

name: Gator Society for Pre-Law Women
purpose: A sisterhood of diverse, accepting, and ambitious women exploring the possibility of a future career in law. This club will assist aspiring female lawyers through guest speakers, LSAT prep workshops, and bimonthly charitable fundraisers.

name: Gator Spikes Roundnet Club
purpose: Gator Spikes Roundnet Club is established for the purpose of developing community, friendship, skills, and to help get more people involved with the sport of Roundnet.

name: Gator Sport Management Organzation
purpose: We provide students looking to work in the sports industry with the skills needed to be successful. To do this, we provide networking opportunities to create the relationships that are crucial in finding work post-graduation.

name: Gator Star Wars
purpose: Gator Star Wars primary purpose is to promote an environment for people to share the same interest in Star Wars, and meet many others with the same passion for the topic. The group will also promote creativity with the creation of outfits and armor inspired by the genre, helping along the way with tips and methods. Our long term goal is to be associated with the Star Wars charity and costuming group known as the 501st Legion, and to eventually be able to do our own form of charity events.

name: Gator Strong Families
purpose: Gator Strong Families exists to work alongside the community's foster families and nonprofits to support and advocate for local children while educating students on the foster care system.
category: Community/Volunteer Service, Social and Global Change

name: Gator Table Tennis Association
purpose: To provide an outlet for students to grow and explore their interest in the sport of table tennis. https://orgs.studentinvolvement.ufl.edu/Forms/sport-clubs

name: Gator UX
purpose: Gator UX is established for the purpose of promoting and teaching the user experience research and design process to anyone who is interested in the field, as well as to help aspiring designers develop professionally.

name: Gator Wealth and Asset Management
purpose: Gator Wealth and Asset Management will aim to teach members about the various tasks wealth and asset managers face on a daily to weekly basis to prepare members for a future career in wealth and asset management and educating the UF community about personal finance by hosting information sessions with guest speakers.

name: Gator Wesley Foundation
purpose: The mission of Gator Wesley is to invite students into an authentic community that encourages a life with Jesus as we discover who we are becoming, and how we are connecting.

name: GatoRaas
purpose: The purpose of GatoRaas is to entertain audiences all around the US by performing traditional Indian Garba/Raas style of dance at a highly competitive level. We are dedicated to preserving the Indian culture through showcasing our unique and vibrant dance form. We hope to encourage diversity and spread awareness of our traditions by performing both on and off campus.

name: GatorCore
purpose: GatorCore was established to serve as a primary resource for those interested in learning core financial industry topics, as well as those interested in careers in finance. Some of the topics covered are financial management, investment banking, real estate, and more. Furthermore, GC strives to transcend the typical barriers of a classroom setting by offering interactive discussions, presentations, guest speakers, and networking opportunities for its members. Finally, GC works to advance the professional development and financial literacy of all members.

name: GatorDays
purpose: GatorDays strives to provide innovative, engaging, affordable, and inclusive events for students at the University of Florida. As a part of the Campus Events and Traditions area of the Department of Student Activities and Involvement, GatorDays will bring programs to students on the UF campus, in the Gainesville community and across of North Central Florida. The leaders and members of this organization will capitalize on students' interests and needs to provide events both on and off-campus that positively contribute to the holistic Gator experience.

name: Gatorloop
purpose: Gatorloop is established for the purpose of developing engineering and business skills and to encourage UF students to participate in competitions relevant to Hyperloop. This organization will also serve to give participating students relevant hands-on experience in each of team's respective divisions, sub-teams, and groups. The purpose of Gatorloop is also to explore and promote academic and career interests related to Hyperloop and related industries.

name: GatorMDA
purpose: GatorMDA is a student-run organization designed to fundraise for the Muscular Dystrophy Association. Our donations support funding research and hosting a week-long summer camp to provide kids with neuromuscular diseases normalcy and fun.

name: GatorSavers
purpose: We are a student organization whose purpose is to spread awareness about the importance of CPR and AED's in the University of Florida campus and greater Gainesville area. We want to inspire individuals to take up roles in promoting this awareness by assisting us in reaching our goal of making Gainesville a heart safe city.

name: Gatortech
purpose: Gatortech is a student community dedicated to learning about the latest technologies. We have regular modules on topics such as cloud computing and web development, as well as speakers and recruiters from various companies.

name: Generation Action
purpose: Planned Parenthood Generation Action (PPGA) is a nonpartisan pro-choice group that organizes events on the University of Florida campus to raise awareness about reproductive and sexual health, support local and national Planned Parenthood health centers, and mobilize advocates of reproductive rights!

name: Generation Sketch Comedy
purpose: Our purpose is to help members improve their writing and acting skills, and give them the experience of producing a sketch comedy show. Members will develop their comedic timing and delivery through peer feedback and support.

name: Generational Relief in Prosthetics
purpose: GRiP is an organization that focuses on making 3D-printed assistive devices, as well as adaptive controllers and toys, for those in need across the world. We also conduct research in a variety of areas and strive to educate the community on STEM through outreach activities. We are open to all majors and no experience is necessary! https://www.grip.bme.ufl.edu

name: Genetic Counseling Club
purpose: The purpose of the Genetic Counseling Club is to foster student's interests and success in a career in genetic counseling. Although UF does not have a genetic counseling program itself, Gainesville is one of the leading cities in genomic research and counseling, providing a myriad of opportunities for students to gain exposure to the field and come in direct contact with the genetic counselors of UF.

name: Gestalt A Cappella
purpose: We are a competitive a cappella group. Our purpose is to represent UF in the a cappella community at large by competing in major competitions (i.e. ICCA, BOSS, SoJam, etc.) while also submitting our music to a cappella award associations (i.e. the CARAs).

name: Girls Who Code at Gainesville
purpose: Girls Who Code is established for the purpose of helping close the gender gap in the computer science field while educating and empowering women by hosting coding workshops, professional development workshops, hackathons, office hours, guest speakers, GBMs, and more.

name: GlamourGals Gainesville
purpose: The purpose of GlamourGals Gainesville is to build empathetic student leaders through companionship and complimentary makeovers to seniors in residential facilities.

name: Global Brigades Public Health
purpose: The purpose of the public health chapter of Global Brigades is to aid in the growth of underserved communities and increase their awareness of public health through an international brigade.

name: Global Business Brigades
purpose: Global Business Brigades is an international movement of university students and professionals building economic opportunities in the developing world. We work alongside promising entrepreneurs and experienced year-round staff to create financial opportunities in remote, rural, and under resourced areas of Panama, Nicaragua, Honduras, and Ghana. We work with communities to build community-owned banks to provide access to loans, savings accounts and financial literacy for community members. Volunteers assist in consulting micro-enterprises, assessing loan capacity payments and providing financial literacy workshops to families.
category: Community/Volunteer Service, Social and Global Change

name: Global Business Society
purpose: To promote awareness of international affairs, the global economy, academic and professional opportunities in international business, to build a global networking community, and to facilitate the integration of international students into the community.

name: Global Connections
purpose: The purpose of the organization shall be: (1) To provide meaningful friendships between international(students/scholars) and American students at The University of Florida. (2) To aid internationals in making meaningful friendships with people in the Gainesville community. (3) To aid internationals in language and cultural adjustments. (4) To aid internationals in temporary home stay and transportation upon arrival. (5) To provide an opportunity for interested international students to learn about Jesus.

name: Global Dental Brigades
purpose: Global Dental Brigades is a non-profit student volunteer organization aimed at allowing students to receive first-hand dental shadowing and volunteering experience in a different country while making a positive impact on the local communities of Honduras, Nicaragua, Panama, and Ghana.

name: Global Engineering Brigades
purpose: Global Engineering Brigades is an international movement of university students and professionals building sustainable clean water solutions in the developing world. We work alongside Professional Engineers and experienced year-round staff to design sustainable water systems in remote, rural, and under-resourced areas of Honduras, Panama, Greece, Nicaragua, and Ghana.

name: Global Legal Empowerment Brigades
purpose: Global Legal Empowerment Brigades is a student-led group that supports Global Brigades in the implementation of a holistic model to meet the legal goals of rural communities in various countries. Along with other GB Chapters on campus, as well as Chapters at other universities, our Chapter participates in year-round recruitment, fundraising, and educational/awareness events that ultimately result in our participation in a 7-9 day brigade, where we actively participate in promoting Legal Empowerment in the communities we work with.

name: Global Medical Brigades
purpose: Global Medical Brigades is an international movement of university students and professionals providing equal access health opportunities in order to diminish disparities in the developing world. We work alongside medical professionals and experienced year-round staff to provide medical and health aid in remote, rural, and under resourced areas of Honduras, Panama, Nicaragua, Ghana, and Greece.
category: Community/Volunteer Service, Social and Global Change

name: Global Medical Missions Alliance
purpose: GMMA's mission statement is to bring and promote Christ-centered missional life to the body of healthcare professionals and its partners. We are a Medical Missions Organization that brings the message of Jesus' healing and love to: - Mobilize mission-minded healthcare professionals to connect what God is doing in the rest of the world - Mentor the next generation of healthcare professionals to move forward in the medical mission field - Network healthcare professionals with global medical missions organizations - Support local church medical mission work across the globe

name: Global Medical Training
purpose: The purposes of this organization are: A. To provide free medical and dental healthcare services and free medicines to the needy in Central America. B. To develop in members basic clinical skills, and basic medical and dental knowledge in preparation for and implementation of the clinics. C. To provide students with a first-hand experience of cultural, social, historical, and political life in these regions. D. To promote awareness of worldwide medical issues in third world countries, which includes the relationship of poverty, education, and public health to personal well-being. E. To raise funds for members to attend medical/dental trips to Central America and to buy medical/dental donations for those trips F. To enhance the interaction between members and other students, faculty, and staff of the University of Florida. G. To provide a social atmosphere for pre-health students interested in international service and to foster an attitude of service in the Gainesville community. H. To sponsor activities in line with the purposes stated above.

name: Global Water Brigades
purpose: Global Water Brigades is an international movement of university students and professionals building economic opportunities in the developing world. We work alongside promising entrepreneurs and experienced year-round staff to create financial opportunities in remote, rural, and under-resourced areas of Honduras, Panama, Greece, Nicaragua, and Ghana.
category: Political Interests, Social and Global Change

name: Golden Key International Honour Society
purpose: Golden Key International Honour Society pushes students to realize their potential through the advancements of academics, leadership, and service. With a focus in community-based events, we strive to open educational and professional doors for our members while simultaneously giving back to the people around us. Golden Key also introduces students to academic leaders who can guide them in achieving career and personal goals. With many opportunities to acquire volunteering and leadership experience, members will be a part of a compassionate community looking to help one another grow. Those interested in our organization may also upgrade to be international members for access to additional scholarships benefits, and connections, however, this is not required to join the UF chapter.

name: Golf Club
purpose: Participation Agreement: https://orgs.studentinvolvement.ufl.edu/Forms/sport-clubs. Our purpose is to compete on a national level, and give students the opportunity to learn and play the game of golf. https://nextgengolf.org/app/teams/university-of-florida-club-golf. We thrive to be the most inclusive club at the University of Florida and encourage all players, no matter of skill level, to join the club and learn more about our sport.

name: GradCru
purpose: GradCru aims to see students invite, invest in, and mobilize each other to declare the good news of Jesus Christ to every graduate student or professional student in every department at the University of Florida. We do this with the hope of eventually putting the gospel within arm's reach of every person on the planet.

name: Graduate Christian Fellowship
purpose: We are a group of graduate students who are intentional about our faith and academics. We strive for a healthy, organic Christian community which is 2-fold: 1) spiritually - the deep questions of life and faith 2) social - having fun together and enjoying life together with organic conversations.

name: Graduate Comics Organization
purpose: We are a graduate student-run organization that serves as a pre-professional and social support group for English graduate students and other graduate students at the University of Florida working on Comics Studies.

name: Graduate Film Studies Group
purpose: To advance the study of film and media studies at the University of Florida.

name: Graduate National Student Speech Language and Hearing Association
purpose: The Graduate National Student Speech Language and Hearing Association is established for the purpose of helping graduate students stay current on advancements in the field, enhance their academic knowledge, find internships and employment, participate in community service activities, promote career awareness, and network with other students with similar interests.

name: Graduate Society of Women Engineers
purpose: We strive to encourage UF's female engineering students to achieve their full potential in careers as engineers and leaders. We host events for developing careers, promoting the presence of women in STEM, and ‹building relationships with other female engineers.

name: Graduate Student Council
purpose: Graduate Student Council was founded with a vision of creating a network for UF graduate students to share resources, build relationships, and enjoy their graduate school experience at UF.

name: Graduate Students in Mass Communication Association
purpose: GSMCA is the organization that represents graduate students, both master's and doctoral, in the University of Florida's College of Journalism and Communications. Its mission is to provide social and educational opportunities for graduate students and to represent our graduate programs across the wider UF community. All graduate students are welcome to get involved and participate in GSMCA's activities.

name: Graham Center Student Fellows
purpose: Our Vision: The Student Fellows work to facilitate relationships and growth through the embodiment of inclusivity, service, activism, and awareness. Our Mission: The Student Fellows work with the Bob Graham Center Staff to create change and lead discussions about today's pressing issues by improving civic health with projects and activities that advance the common good of all communities.
category: Political Interests, Social and Global Change, Special Interests

name: GREBE Audubon Campus Chapter
purpose: We are an organization focused on avian conservation, identification, and education through academia, community service, and networking.

name: Green Building Club
purpose: Green Building Club connects students that are passionate about sustainable construction, LEED design, and climate action so that they may become better equipped to make a difference in our planet's future.

name: Green Greeks Florida
purpose: The purpose of Green Greeks Florida is to reduce waste, conserve energy, prevent pollution, and encourage the greek community and all students to take action to better the environment and the campus.

name: Green STEM
purpose: The purpose of Green STEM is to educate students on prominent environmental issues and explore solutions together through service, scientific research, and technological advancement.
category: Social and Global Change, Special Interests

name: Greenhouse College
purpose: Greenhouse College Ministry is established for the purpose of serving all students at the University of Florida by connecting them with the local community in weekly gatherings, microchurches, and discipleship as passionate followers of Jesus.

name: Handbuilt or Thrown Clay
purpose: H.O.T. Clay (Handbuilt Or Thrown) is a student organization comprised of current students of the University of Florida School of Art + Art History. The mission of H.O.T. Clay is to increase the awareness and understanding of the ceramic arts. We hold regular meetings, where the membership mobilizes to organize sales of ceramic works to raise funds for various projects. These projects include: funding student travel to the annual NCECA conference, visiting artist programming, guest lectures and more. Student members work together to choose visiting artists, and sponsor the visiting artist events. Planning and implementation of H.O.T.
